<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have yet to see this spell in action but from what I gather its an emergency type song.  If it were a spell I would rarely waste 1/8th of my spell potential on a spell I'd cast once an hour. <P>So now you would have to know 15 minute in advance that your having an emergency?  Seams like the problem could be fixed by making mana regen to full in about 15 mintues and leave everything else alone.  <P>Seams silly that they cant get back mana from clarity, even though they can sing a song to make everyone elses go up.  <P>You can say that Bard mana is not the same. Well neither is cleric mana the same as say wizard mana. One is god granted, the other is focusing of the mental powers.  Mana is just an abstract way to describing magic potential. One for which I would think bards would have figured out to increase way before they worked on increasing the mana of those around them.  <P>Thats just my opinion of course.<P>Any bards out there try a mana stone or rod of modulation yet? Then heal song?<P>-Rezek<P><BR>
