<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Okay, I don't usually post on matters like this, but this one really jumps out at me. See, I belive it would really be a waste to have to keep dirge memmed for 15 mins before I could use it each time. As it is, with the new charm, I never use it anymore, but if I had to dedicate a song gem to dirge, there'd be NO chance of it ever coming out of retirement. The song is not worth keeping memmed all the time, especially when you consider the amount of useful songs that a bard has at his disposal at any given moment. I think the best way to fix this would be to regen mana to full every 15 mins. That way it's keeping track of the time, even when you don't have it memmed. Then when you're full and want to use it, you can just mem it up, fire and forget. Sure, it's still kind of a waste considering how good charm is (by the way, isn't that supposed to be refreshable, if not, why does it lower magic resist?). It's 2:30 in the morning now, Kunark is good, but my coherency is not. Keeping songs memmed for 15 mins before being able to use them = bad. Slow mana regen = bad. That is all.<P>Junon
</FONT>
