Well, I'm still a relatively inexperienced bard and won't have this song for some time.  But I've been following the thread of discussion on the thing for a while.<P>Personally, I think a timer is better than mana usage, but the timer should start when the song is sung, go 15 minutes, then allow it to be sung again after that.  Period.  Not get reset when the song is -memmed- as well.  You could find yourself waiting a half hour that way if you need to swap the thing out.  And what's wrong with only triggering the timer when it's actually sung?  That should work just fine, yes?
