<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have seen bards use this song and I actually like the way they use it.  Yes it is for emergency situations but these are not so infrequent that keeping this song up is not useful.  We have all seen a mob simply NOT leave a target.  Say it gets on the healer and won't leave him/her alone.  I have seen cases like this where a bard friend tries to charm or mez the mob but it resist too much.  Then he whips out his dirge, nukes it and now the mob is pissed at him freeing up the healer to heal self then bard while the rest of us keep killing the mob.  This is just one example.  Another would be in evac situation where multiple mobs start hitting the evacer.  My bard friend fears as much as he can and dirges the rest onto him so we can get the hell out of dodge.  Solo bards could use it as that big punch at the beginning to help even the odds, repeat every 15 min.  Being in a low level dungeon that still aggroes(example MM or unrest) would be nice to clear a few mobs with an AE song like dirge.  I am sure there are other uses I have not seen for this song.
</FONT>
