Considering I have effectively 5 song slots available to work with (Selos, Clarity, and Healing are a given), and that I can keep 3 to 4 songs up at any given time.  That leaves 1 slot available for a "utility" type song.  I generally fill this slot with charm or pixie (mez).  Also considering I "cast" (sing a different song) every THREE seconds during battle, is it worth it to me to use my ONE available slot for a song I have to wait 15 minutes to be able to use and then only be able to use it every 15 minutes?<P>Well, if it REALLY was a Despirate Dirge, and REALLY did some damage, the answer might be yes!  My cleric friend the same level with Retribution can do 600+ damage.  DDD does 311.  But let's face it gang, when you are dealing with mobs at 4000+ HP, does this song do much even if you CAN cast/sing it every 15 minutes?<P>IMHO not worth that one very valuable spell slot, when instead I can charm another MOB to do a great deal more then 311 points damage, or mez while my blaster friends med so they can hit it with something that truly will make a difference.<P>Menoly<BR>44th Bard of E'ci
