<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Mana should be a part of bards... our songs are magical by their very nature.  However, it does seem ridiculous to wait 15 minutes to use a song that you just memorized.  Being in that '8th utility slot', I could swap to some other song that would be much more useful to a situation.  I change my 8th song a lot, depending on where I am and what I'm doing next.  I agree with the idea that it should be available immediate after memorization, then unavailable for 15 minutes regardless if you try to forget and remem it.  Otherwise just leave it using mana.  Or better yet, make the dirge and brauvara cost MORE mana, but give us access to normal mana recovery rates (ie. clarity, manastone, meditation).  Don't make it more useless than it is.  Right now, it's mostly a bonus weapon while soloing.  I could also see it as a mega-taunt to free your healer or evacuator.  But if I have to wait 15 minutes from memorization, you can bet it'll almost never find it's way into my memory.  Of course, Lucid Lullaby would be a much nicer alternative if it actually worked and kept a mob mezzed when it says it does.<P>In short, I guess the options at hand don't matter much to me.  It's generally not useful enough to warrant a spot on the mem list unless I'm soloing for a long period.  Heh, maybe if I'm camping a low level spawn with a 15 minute spawn rate.   <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><P>Nexroth<BR>Cazic-Thule Troubador of the Berserker Crescendo<P>------------------<BR>"I believe I've past the age of consciousness and righteous rage; I've found that just surviving is a noble fight." - Billy Joel
