<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
OK. Lot of debate going on here. I have a possible solution that I hope is not too hard to code for the EQ code monkeys.<P>If I'm not mistaken, the current Dirge does 300+ damage to all targets within its radius(to a maximum of 4 targets); party members included. For a 43rd level spell, this amount is really insulting. My proposal is this....make the damage the total POTENTIAL of the current damage, so the damage would be 1200+ points. Now, the damage is DISTRIBUTED to anything within the radius of the song RADIATING OUT from the Bard, but not including the Bard. For example,<P>Bard is in full group. He is singing primarily healing and clarity. The battle is quickly heading south, the target being 2 or 3 upper 40 MOBS. The group manages to kill all but one, but the other is still at half when it becomes clear that the group will lose. The Bard, being a good Bard, shouts, "OK folks. I'm gonna taunt(with some hi-taunt AoE song), run (clear area with Selos), and Dirge. Lay off!" The Bard then taunts, activates Selos and runs to a clear spot, his group moving the other way. He now has the half dead(but still potent) MOB on him alone. He sings DDD. The MOB takes 1200 points and dies. Hooray for the Bard! If both MOBs were still up they would each take 600pts. 3 MOBs...well you get it.<P>15 minutes, or 30 minutes later the Bard can sing it again.<P>The Bard has to be extremely good to make this work. If he moves to a spot with even the lowest level critter already there, he reduces the damage on his song. Killing a snake with 600+ points would make me angry and probably kill me as my intended target(s) would mush me. And also, it only works if the Bard CAN taunt the mob away.<P>OK. Another bonus for the Bard: he can now solo higher level mobs a little better. Get one HG alone in the song's radius and wack him for 1200pts and then MAYBE you can kite him to death. But of course, this can only be done every 15, 30, 60 minutes, whatever recast time Verant wants to put there.<P>OK. I'm sorry for the long post and I know I'm a bit off-topic, but DDD (as it is) is a waste of a song slot. 15 minute timer (and no mana) or not, this one is a sick dog and should be put to sleep.
</FONT>
