</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
&gt;&gt;&gt; Holy mother, yeah, the ability to smack down 320 damage AE every 15 minutes would work.&lt;&lt;&lt;<P>I am of the opinion that anything mana related does not belong to the Bard. But (I am not that high yet) we have so many good songs that can do damage, via other party members ... what is the point? That we want this so we could solo and get a large push when we want to take down Giants?<P>What I find strange is that if we put on an instrument, and use the other 2 DoT's, we can do so much more damage than 320 points in 15 minutes ... in fact more like 2,000/2,500 points in that time. AND no mana used.<P>Can someone explain the usage of something like this? In my book this belongs to the casters, not to the Bards. I have my doubts about using this, if it is going to hurt the whole party in the end. Pretty soon, they will tie up the mana restoration song to mana itself, and there goes the Bard right down the tube. 
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
